(4, 3, 'Procurement of Non-Medical Consumables - Surgicals', 'Procurement of Non-Medical Consumables - Surgicals - Various', '0.00', 'All tenders must be accompanied by:\n1. Valid Certificate of Incorporation\n2. Valid Certificate of Commencement of Business\n3. Renewal of Business Registration Receipt 2019\n4. Valid VAT Certificate of Registration or Evidence of Exemption from VAT \n5. Valid Tax Clearance Certificate - Valid as at 01/01/2019\n6. Valid SSNIT Clearance Certificate - Valid As At 01/01/2019\n7. Valid Food and Drugs Authority Certificate\n8. Valid Public Procurement Authority Registration Certificate/Receipt\n9. Other valid documents\n\nDelivery Period - 21 Days from Date of Award\nTender Security - 2% of Total Tender Value', '2019-06-29', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 19:54:11', '2019-03-18 19:54:11'),
(5, 3, 'Supply & Installation of 240 Litre Wheeled Bin With Metal Cage', 'The Ministry of Sanitation and Water Resources intends to apply part of its budgetary allocation to fund eligible payments under the contract for Supply and Installation of 240 Litre Wheeled Bin with Metal Cage as indicated below;\n\nLot 1:	240 Litre Wheeled Bin with Metal Cage - Qty 1,000 units\nLot 2:	240 Litre Wheeled Bin with Metal Cage - Qty 1,000 units', '0.00', 'Eligible suppliers must have the following valid documents:\n\na.	Certificate of Registration within the Republic of Ghana,\nb.	Certificate of Registration to commence business within the Republic of Ghana,\nc.	GRA Clearance Certificate\nd.	Value Added Tax (VAT) Certificate\ne.	SSNIT Certificate and\nf.	PPA Registration Certificate \n\nDelivery Period : 40 Days\nTender Security : 2% of Tender Price', '2019-07-30', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 19:56:52', '2019-03-18 19:56:52'),
(6, 3, 'Procurement of Vehicles', '2.	Cocoa Marketing Company (Gh.) Limited therefore invites sealed Tenders from eligible suppliers for the supply of the above-mentioned items. Tendering will be conducted through the National Competitive Tendering (NCT) procedures specified in the Public Procurement Act 2003, (Act 663) as amended and the Guidelines issued by the Public Procurement Authority (PPA) of the Republic of Ghana.\n\n3.	Tenderers shall quote for all quantities in a Lot (of a package). Tenders not offering all quantities in the lot shall be declared non-responsive. \n\n4.	Interested eligible Tenderers may obtain further information from the Deputy Procurement Manager , Cocoa Marketing Company (Gh.) Limited, Room 11, First Floor of the Swanzy Shopping Arcade from Monday, 11th March, 2019 between 8.30am and 4.30pm local time onwards till the close of tender.\n\n5.	A complete set of Tender document in English may be purchased by interested tenderers on the submission of a written application to the address below and upon payment of a non-refundable fee of Four Hundred and Fifty Ghana Cedis (GH�450.00) payable at the Cash Office, Room 207, Second Floor, Cocoa House - Accra. The method of payment will be by cash or bank draft payable to Cocoa Marketing Company (Gh.) Limited. \n\n6.	Tenders must be delivered to the address below on or before 10.30 am. on the closing date for the submission of tender. Tenders shall be valid for a period of 120 days after deadline for Tender submission. All Tenders must be accompanied by a Tender Security of not less than Two percent (2%) of the Total Tender Price from a reputable Bank. Tender security shall be in the currency of the tender. \n\n7.	Tenders will be opened in the presence of Tenderers and/or their representatives who choose to attend at the Board Room, Room 306, 3rd Floor, Cocoa House, at 10.45 am on the day of tender submission.', '0.00', 'Valid (Current) Business Registration Documents\nValid Tax Clearance Certificate\nValid SSNIT Certificate\nValid VAT Registration Certificate \nValid PPA Supplier Registration Certificate\n\nPlease note that all documents shall be valid at the time of tender closure.\n\nAddress for further information or clarification:\n\nThe Managing Director\nCocoa Marketing Company (Gh.) Limited\nP.O Box 1017\nAccra, Ghana \n\nLocation for Tender Submission: \n\nCocoa Marketing Company (Gh.) Limited\n3rd Floor Main Reception, Cocoa House\nKwame Nkrumah Avenue, Accra.\nDigital Address: GA-105-0575\nAccra-Ghana\n\nTelephone Nos. : 233-0302-668281\n233-0302-668352\n233-0302-668464\n\nE-mail: info@cocoamarketing.com \n\n\nLate Tenders shall be rejected.', '2019-08-21', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 19:59:34', '2019-03-18 19:59:34'),
(7, 1, 'Construction of Police Station', 'The North Tongu District Assembly in the Volta Region of the Republic of Ghana, has received budgetary allocation from its District Assembly Common Fund and intends to use part of the budgetary allocation to cover eligible payment for works contracts whose requirements are indicated below;\n\nConstruction Of 1 No. Police Station At Volo', '0.00', 'Tender Security - 2% of Tender Price', '2019-06-01', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 20:01:37', '2019-03-18 20:01:37'),
(8, 1, 'Re-Roofing Of Basic School', 'The North Tongu District Assembly in the Volta Region of the Republic of Ghana, has received budgetary allocation from its District Assembly Common Fund and intends to use part of the budgetary allocation to cover eligible payment for works contracts whose requirements are indicated below;\n\nRe-Roofing Of Podoe E. P. Basic School At Podoe', '5000.00', 'Tender Security - 2% of Tender Price', '2019-06-24', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 20:04:32', '2019-03-18 20:04:32'),
(9, 3, 'Supply of Laboratory Environment Monitoring Device through Framework Contracting', 'The Food and Drugs Authority invites sealed Tenders from eligible registered suppliers for the supply of Laboratory Environmental Monitoring Devices through Framework Contracting as per requirements below;\n\n1. Datalogger - Qty 22\n2. Thermohygrometer - Qty 30\n3. Thermometer - Qty 9', '0.00', 'Tender Security : 2% of Tender Price', '2019-05-25', 'GH', NULL, '2019-03-18 20:07:16', '2019-03-18 20:07:16'),
(10, 3, 'Provision of cleaning services', 'NATIONAL COMPETITIVE TENDERING\nFOR THE PROVISION OF CLEANING SERVICES, WASTE COLLECTION SERVICES, WEED CONTROL SERVICES AND DISLODGING OF SEPTIC TANKS AT THE HOSPITAL PREMISES AND SOME SELECTED STAFF RESIDENCES\n\nCLEANING SERVICES CONTRACT PACKAGE NUMBER: AR/KATH/NCT/GS/002/001/19\n\nWASTE COLLECTION SERVICES CONTRACT PACKAGE NUMBER: AR/KATH/NCT/GS/001/001/19\n\nWEED CONTROL SERVICES CONTRACT PACKAGE NUMBER: AR/KATH/NCT/GS/015/001/19\n\nDISLODGING OF SEPTIC TANKS CONTRACT PACKAGE NUMBER: AR/KATH/NCT/GS/004/001/19\n\nThe Hospital Management and Tender Committee intend to apply part of its budgetary allocation to fund eligible payments under the contract for the provision of Cleaning, Waste Collection and Weed Control Services in support of quality healthcare delivery to our clients. \n\n1.	Your company/enterprise is hereby invited to participate in the tendering process by applying to the Director of Administration, KATH for a set of tender documents at a non-refundable fee of GH� 300.00 for each document. \n\n2.	This invitation is open to Ghanaian Registered firms who experience in Cleaning, Waste Collection and Weed Control Services. The details of areas/locations earmarked for Cleaning Services, Waste collection, Weed control services and Dislodging of Septic Tanks are indicated in the Tender Document. \n\n3.	The Cleaning Services Include: \n\n1. Cleaning Services within the Hospital Premises\n2. Cleaning at KATH Residential Premises\n\n4.	The Waste Collection and Disposal Services Include:\n\n1. Collection and disposal of Waste from the Hospital Premises\n2. Collection and disposal of Waste from the Residential Premises\n\n5.	The Weed Control Services Include:\n\n1.	Weeding/Mowing\n2.	Slashing, Trimming and Spraying weedicides on some pavements\n\n6.	Dislodging of Septic Tanks at the Hospital and Some Selected Staff Residences.\n\n7.	Tenderers are required to submit the following Mandatory Requirements:\n\na.	Tender Form Signed\nb.	Business registration certificate and certificate to commence business issued by the Registrar-Generals department, Ghana.\nc.	The object clause authorising the firm to engage in waste collection, cleaning, weed control and dislodging services.\nd.	VAT Registration Certificate \ne.	Valid/current tax Clearance Certificate (valid up to May,2019)\nf.	Valid SSNIT Contribution Certificate (valid up to May,2019)\ng.	Valid labour certificate (valid up to May,2019)\n\n\n\n\nh.	Tender Security (2% of total price)\ni.	Evidence of Public Procurement Authority Registration\n\n8.	Interested tenderers are advised to inspect copies of the tender document at the Procurement Unit, KATH from 8:00 am to 4:00pm before the purchase of the tender document.\n\n9.	Tenderers are to submit their tenders at the Office of the Director of Administration, KATH.\n\n10.	The closing date for submission of the tender is 14th May, 2019 at 10:00am prompt. Late tenders will be rejected.\n\n11.	Tender opening will follow immediately after the closing time of submission of tenders at 10:00am at the address below:\n\nFamily Planning Conference Room\nKomfo Anokye Teaching Hospital\nKumasi\n\n12.	The contract would be governed by the Instruction to tenderers, General Conditions of Contract, and Special Conditions of Contract, Specification indicated and the Technical & Financial Proposals submitted by tenderers.\n\n13.	There will be pre-tender conference for all prospective tenderers schedule for 2nd May, 2019 at 10:00am, the venue is Family Planning Conference Room.', '100000.00', 'a.	Tender Form Signed\nb.	Business registration certificate and certificate to commence business issued by the Registrar-Generals department, Ghana.\nc.	The object clause authorising the firm to engage in waste collection, cleaning, weed control and dislodging services.\nd.	VAT Registration Certificate \ne.	Valid/current tax Clearance Certificate (valid up to May,2019)\nf.	Valid SSNIT Contribution Certificate (valid up to May,2019)\ng.	Valid labour certificate (valid up to May,2019)\n\n\n\n\nh.	Tender Security (2% of total price)\ni.	Evidence of Public Procurement Authority Registration\n\n8.	Interested tenderers are advised to inspect copies of the tender document at the Procurement Unit, KATH from 8:00 am to 4:00pm before the purchase of the tender document.\n\n9.	Tenderers are to submit their tenders at the Office of the Director of Administration, KATH.', '2019-05-08', 'GH', NULL, '2019-04-29 02:29:55', '2019-04-29 02:29:55'),
